== Trademark Policy ==
Version: 1.0 <br />
Published: 22 February 2019

{{name}} owns a number of trademarks in both word and logo form including brands, slogans, styles. This policy encompasses all marks, in word and logo form, collectively referred to as "{{software-name}} trademarks". You can see a non-exhaustive list of {{software-name}} trademarks, including both registered and unregistered (but otherwise legally recognized) trademarks at in chapter [[#Trademarks|Trademarks]].

The objective of this trademark policy is:

1. to encourage widespread use and adoption of the {{software-name}} trademarks,<br />
2. to clarify proper usage of {{software-name}} trademarks by third parties,<br />
3. to prevent misuse of {{software-name}} trademarks that can confuse or mislead users with respect to {{software-name}} or its affiliates.

Please note that it is not the goal of this policy to limit commercial activity around {{software-name}}. We encourage businesses to work on {{software-name}} while being compliant with this policy.

Following are the guidelines for the proper use of {{software-name}} trademarks by publishers and other third parties. Any use of or reference to {{software-name}} trademarks that is inconsistent with these guidelines, or other unauthorized use of or reference to {{software-name}} trademarks, or use of marks that are confusingly similar to {{software-name}} trademarks, is prohibited and may violate {{software-name}} trademark rights.

Any use of {{software-name}} trademarks in a misleading and false manner or in a manner that disparages {{software-name}}, such as untruthful advertising, is always prohibited.

== When You Can Use the {{software-name}} Trademarks Without Asking Permission ==
1. You can use {{software-name}} trademarks to make true factual statements about {{software-name}} or communicate compatibility with your product truthfully.<br />
2. Your intended use qualifies as "nominative fair use" of the {{software-name}} trademarks, i.e., merely identifying that you are talking about {{software-name}} in a text, without suggesting sponsorship or endorsement.<br />
3. You can use {{software-name}} trademarks to describe or advertise your services or products relating to {{software-name}} in a way that is not misleading.<br />
4. You can use {{software-name}} trademarks to describe {{software-name}} in articles, titles or blog posts.<br />
5. You can make t-shirts, desktop wallpapers, caps, or other merchandise with {{software-name}} trademarks for both, commercial and non-commercial usage.<br />
6. You can also make merchandise with {{software-name}} trademarks for both, commercial and non-commercial usage. In case of commercial usage, we recommend that you truthfully advertise to customers which part of the selling price, if any, will be paid to the {{software-name}} project. See our [[Payments]] page for more information on how to donate to the {{software-name}} project.<br />

== When You Can NEVER Use the {{software-name}} Trademarks Without Asking Permission ==

1. You cannot use {{software-name}} trademarks in any way that suggests an affiliation with or endorsement by the {{software-name}} project or community, if the same is not true.<br />
2. You cannot use {{software-name}} trademarks in a company or organization name or as the name of a product or service.<br />
3. You cannot use a name that is confusingly similar to {{software-name}} trademarks.<br />
4. You cannot use {{software-name}} trademarks in a domain name, with or without commercial intent.<br />

== How to Use the {{software-name}} Trademarks ==

1. Use the {{software-name}} trademarks in a manner that makes it clear that your project is related to the {{software-name}} project, but that it is not part of {{software-name}}, produced by the {{software-name}} project, or endorsed by the {{software-name}} project.

2. Acknowledge {{name}}'s ownership of the {{software-name}} trademark prominently.

Example:

<blockquote>
[TRADEMARK] is a trademark owned by {{name}}.
</blockquote>

3. Include a disclaimer of sponsorship, affiliation, or endorsement by {{software-name}} on your website and on all related printed materials.

Example:

<blockquote>
X PROJECT is not affiliated with {{software-name}}. {{software-name}} is a trademark owned by {{name}}.
</blockquote>

4. Distinguish the {{software-name}} trademarks from the surrounding words by italicizing, bolding or underlining it.

5. Use the {{software-name}} trademarks in their exact form, neither abbreviated or hyphenated, nor combined with any other word or words.

6. Do not create acronyms using the {{software-name}} trademarks.

== Permission To Use ==

When in doubt about the use of {{software-name}} trademarks, or to request permission for uses not allowed by this policy, please send an email to {{name-email}} with subject "Trademark Use Request"; be sure to include the following information in the body of your message:

* Name of the User
* Name of the organization/project
* Purpose of Use (commercial/non-commercial)
* Nature of Use

== Newer Versions of this Policy ==

This policy may be revised from time to time and updated versions shall be available at https://www.{{project_clearnet}}/wiki/{{project_name_short}}_Trademark_Policy.

== Guidelines for Using Logos ==

* Any scaling must retain the original proportions of the logo.
* Do not use the {{software-name}} logos as part of your company logo or product logo or branding itself. They can be used as part of a page describing your products or services.
* You need not ask us for permission to use logos on your own website solely as a hyperlink to the {{software-name}} project website.

For any queries with respect to these guidelines, please send an email to {{name-email}}.

